Two suspects appeared at the Nsuze Magistrates Court in KwaZulu-Natal on Thursday for possession of unlicensed firearms and ammunition, police said. Police spokesperson colonel Thembeka Mbele said Ilembe Crime Intelligence members, together with the Ilembe Cluster Task team, had conducted an operation at Nodunga, Oqaqeni and Emambedwini Reserves in Mapumulo. Mbele said they arrested two suspects, aged 28 and 50, for possession of unlicensed firearms and ammunition. The suspects were arrested at the Emambedwini and Nodunga areas for possession of a 9mm Norinco Star pistol, 9mm Star pistol, one magazine and ten rounds of ammunition, Mbele said. Both suspects were detained at Maphumulo Police Station. All recovered firearms would be sent for ballistics tests to establish if they were used in any other crimes in the province. African News Agency For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.